import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['age'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_freq = data['name'].value_counts()
    age_freq = data.groupby('age').size()
    age_freq = age_freq.reindex(np.arange(age_freq.index.min(), age_freq.index.max()+1)).fillna(0)
    plt.plot(age_freq.index, age_freq.values, label='Name Frequency')
    plt.plot(name_freq.index, name_freq.values, label='Age Frequency')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and name frequency?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
